<p><b>A WEEKLY TIP ON CARING FOR OUR COMMON HOME</b>.
Of the estimated 29 billion gallons of water used daily
by households in the US, nearly 9 billion gallons
(30%) is used outdoors. In the hot summer months,
that percentage often goes up to 70%. You can help
change that by replacing part of your lawn with native
and drought resistant plants.</p>

